news.title: Kerala government to prepare GIS maps of properties
news.para: LSGD has issued an order for the digital mapping of properties based on the recommendation of the sixth state finance commission (SSFC). There should be separate markings for public and private properties, SSFC had said in its report.

news.title: Bhubaneswar civic body to set up construction waste processing unit
news.para: The civic body has invited a tender to select an agency that will not only set up the plant but will also be responsible for its operation and maintenance.

news.title: Civic body serves property tax notices on Lucknow mall, hotel
news.para: The LMC officials said that the tax notices were served to the Lulu mall a week ago and to the Centrum hotel in February.

news.title: Visakhapatnam development body issues notification to sell 37 plots
news.para: These plots are spread in its various layouts in the combined Visakhapatnam and Vizianagaram districts. The base prices of these plots range between 14,000 and 55,000 depending on the location. Some plots measure as high as 800 square yards.

news.title: Google leases 1-lakh-sq-ft flexible office space in Pune's Mundhwa
news.para: The new office at commercial tower Amar Pristine 81 (AP81) near Koregaon Park Annex will be utilised by Google to operate its cloud computing business and is expected to house more than 1,300 employees.

news.title: In Kolkata, Hidco to rent out 53,000 sq ft co-living, co-working space
news.para: The complex has two blocks, one for living and another for working. The co-living space has a covered area of about 4,624 sq m while the co-working space has a covered area of 3,070 sq m.

news.title: Over 1,300 more buildings have come up without fire NOC: Nagpur civic body survey
news.para: The NMC’s fire department has started initiating action against violators under the Maharashtra Fire Prevention and Life Safety Measures Act, 2006.

news.title: Builder may have to pay double for bounced cheque: Mumbai court
news.para: The directors of Prisha Developers Pvt Ltd, Sonali Ugle, Rajaram Bandekar and Kiran Gupte were also sentenced to six months' imprisonment each in both cases. "...merely having order of consumer court in favour of complainant is no ground to show leniency to the accused," metropolitan magistrate K G Sawant said.

news.title: Telangana HC relief for Sahithi Infra Tech Ventures, says no to multiple FIRs
news.para: The first FIR should be treated as the main case and the statements of complainants in all the subsequent FIRs should be added to the first FIR, said a bench of Chief Justice Ujjal Bhuyan and Justice N Tukaramji.

news.title: Kanpur development body to use DGNSS for demarcating its properties
news.para: KDA vice-chairman Arvind Singh after a presentation given on Friday by its developer directed to use this digital technology first in the New Kanpur City being developed by the Authority between Mainavati Road and Kalyanpur-Bithoor Road.

news.title: Nashik civic body collects Rs 152 crore property tax in FY23
news.para: Officials of the Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) said one of the main reasons for the record property tax collection is that several new properties have been brought under the property tax net.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body budget: Focus on ongoing projects, no hike in property tax
news.para: The total expenditure of the civic body is pegged at Rs 4,922.5 crore while the expected revenue is Rs 4,925 crore. There will be no hike in the property tax yet again—18th year in a row.

news.title: Jaipur: JMC-G cracks whip on urban development tax defaulters
news.para: The corporation has identified around 85 properties in each zone so far where UD tax ranging from Rs 10,000 to up to Rs 1 lakh is pending. Most of these properties are in Malviya Nagar and Jagatpura zones.

news.title: Over 4,500 properties sealed in Ahmedabad for pending property tax dues
news.para: The tax and revenue department sealed 1,761 properties located in the west zone, the highest number of properties sealed zone wise. AMC said that 720 properties were sealed in the east zone and 739 in the north-west zone.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: Handing over of five lakh houses likely by March-end
news.para: The officials told chief minister Y S Jagan Mohan Reddy on Friday that works are in progress to complete the infrastructure as well for these houses.
